d like to try to take him down.  Only think I'm interested in is his shell piece for a shield quest<br><br>Properties<br>MAGIC ITEM  LORE ITEM  QUEST RELATED   <br>Type, Slot                              Armor, Shield <br>Armor Class                            23 <br>Boosts                                  +10 STR, +5 CHA, +10 WIS, -5 AGI, +20 FR, +20 CR, +10 MR <br><br>Effect: Enduring Breath <br>Weight &amp; Size                       WT: 5.0  Size: ? <br>Class WAR, CLR, PAL, RNG, SHD, DRU, BRD, ROG, SHM <br>Race    ALL <br><br><br>I'm mainly interested in it for the Wis and the EB effect.<br><br>The Turtle has many other nice drops that the people who help me are willing to duel each other for. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub55.ezboard.com/umystipul.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mystipul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>KoV Friend</span><br>  Posts: 84<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(2/18/02 11:57:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub55.ezboard.com/fknightsofvalor76584frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/blackmist2/blkuni4.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Lodizal</span><hr size=1> hehehehehehe... This turtle is the most sought after spawn in almost all of norrath!.... Most guilds such as Red sky, HON, and a few others have low level mules staked out either in zone, or at the little gnoll camp just WAITING for him to spawn his sorry butt. and within less than 5 minutes of his spawnage... 2 to 4 guilds have converged on him and fight to see who can tag him first.. and even once taged does not mean another guild will not KS his ass out from under you.  And No. a GM won't do Sqwat about it.  Who ever kills him gets to loot him<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>He always drops 6 things.   USUALLY, the piece for the eye patch of plunder, Lodizal boots, 1 or 2 pieces of Shell for the Lodizal shield quest, and high level spells. and sometimes a stray item here and there.<br><br><br>As for fighting him.  3 groups of UNDER 55, or 2 groups 55, or 1 group 60.  He can be slowed, so a shaman is nice.. he can be Kited .. have a druid track and tag his ass and pull him away from other guilds gathering or to where your guild is.  He hits fairly hard but a good tank can kick his wussy butt.... SO mainly 2 or 3 tanks, shaman, druid, and healers, and of course the Porters to get you there as SOON as possible.   This is not something that spawns and sits... usually within 30 minutes of him spawning he is dead.. regardless of time of day that he spawns.  ALSO.. I think spawn time has changed to Random with the latest patch where they changed all uber godly highly sought after mobs to Random instead of static spawnage....<br><br>*waves* <p></br><a href="http://members.aol.com/blackmist2/index.htm" target="_blank"><img src="http://members.aol.com/blackmist2/sig2.jpg" border="0"></a> <br>Oracle Mystipul Myst'Rakkastaja<br>Phantom Raiders<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub55.ezboard.com/ubascomb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>bascomb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>KoV member</span><br>  Posts: 207<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(2/19/02 6:47:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub55.ezboard.com/fknightsofvalor76584frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Lodizal</span><hr size=1> Oh - ok - well looks like I Want a piece of what everybody else wants as usual. =)<br><br>Bas <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=titl